  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "2002-04-09", 
    "text": "Corporate Asset Protection Act of 2002 - Amends the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 to prohibit a reporting issuer (registrant on a national securities exchange) from offering or providing a loan to an insider unless: (1) the issuer is a financial institution; and (2) the terms are not substantially more advantageous than those offered to non-insiders. Prescribes civil penalties for violation of such prohibition."
